1990
01:16:19,532 --> 01:16:20,999
- Let's take Polaroids.
- Polaroid?

1991
01:16:21,000 --> 01:16:22,567
- Over there.
- Let's take one as a group

1992
01:16:22,568 --> 01:16:23,936
- and photograph the food.
- Yeah.

1993
01:16:24,403 --> 01:16:25,603
This is the main dish for sure.

1994
01:16:25,604 --> 01:16:27,606
<i>- This is crazy.
- Let me snap a shot.</i>

1995
01:16:29,141 --> 01:16:30,208
That's what I always do.

1996
01:16:30,209 --> 01:16:32,278
- I'm blown away.
- Mischievous chef.

1997
01:16:33,445 --> 01:16:35,113
SATISFIED

1998
01:16:35,114 --> 01:16:37,215
SOBER

1999
01:16:37,216 --> 01:16:38,416
I'll cut the arm now.

2000
01:16:38,417 --> 01:16:39,685
- Okay.
- All right.

2001
01:16:40,019 --> 01:16:41,553
It's a shame about that.

2002
01:16:41,554 --> 01:16:43,221
- That's enormous.
- My gosh.

2003
01:16:43,222 --> 01:16:46,090
They say octopus is great
for boosting energy.

2004
01:16:46,091 --> 01:16:47,992
- Right, for our health...
- I've got to have some.

2005
01:16:47,993 --> 01:16:49,794
- So true.
- It restores your energy.

2006
01:16:49,795 --> 01:16:51,095
This one's the good stuff.

2007
01:16:51,096 --> 01:16:52,630
- Taurine?
- Taurine.

2008
01:16:52,631 --> 01:16:55,099
SUDDENLY INTERESTED
AFTER LEARNING ITS HEALTH BENEFITS

2009
01:16:55,100 --> 01:16:57,035
Add octopus slices
to your breakfast cereal.

2010
01:16:57,036 --> 01:16:58,603
Sure, have them with milk.

2011
01:16:58,604 --> 01:16:59,904
Yes, people do that with cereals.

2012
01:16:59,905 --> 01:17:01,272
Have some when drinking water, too.

2013
01:17:01,273 --> 01:17:03,541
From now on, all our dishes
will have octopus in them.

2014
01:17:03,542 --> 01:17:05,843
Let's enjoy them
while we still have good teeth.

2015
01:17:05,844 --> 01:17:07,679
AT THIS RATE, THEY'LL EAT ROCKS
IF THEY'RE HEALTHY

2016
01:17:07,680 --> 01:17:10,148
You can also use the octopus stock

2017
01:17:10,149 --> 01:17:11,283
to wash your face.

2018
01:17:12,051 --> 01:17:14,218
- It's too good to waste.
- Do-yeon, let's soak our hands in it

2019
01:17:14,219 --> 01:17:16,221
- for therapy.
- That will heal us in no time.

2020
01:17:17,656 --> 01:17:20,659
WHILE EVERYONE'S THOUGHTS
ARE FOCUSED ON HEALTH

2021
01:17:21,293 --> 01:17:23,796
THIS GUY ONLY CARES ABOUT THE TASTE

2022
01:17:24,163 --> 01:17:28,066
A LOT OF THOUGHT WENT INTO PLANNING
THEIR FIRST FAMILY MEAL

2023
01:17:28,067 --> 01:17:29,867
Let me serve this for you.

2024
01:17:29,868 --> 01:17:31,736
A PRESSURE HE'S NEVER EXPERIENCED
AS A SOLO DWELLER

2025
01:17:31,737 --> 01:17:34,739
- Thank you for the food.
- I'll enjoy them.

2026
01:17:34,740 --> 01:17:36,075
Man, I'm so excited.

2027
01:17:36,675 --> 01:17:38,510
SOO-JIN TAKES A BITE FIRST

2028
01:17:39,411 --> 01:17:40,746
Who arranged this so nicely?

2029
01:17:41,447 --> 01:17:43,048
AUTOMATIC CLAPPING

2030
01:17:43,349 --> 01:17:45,117
- Is it okay?
- It's to die for.

2031
01:17:45,451 --> 01:17:46,551
I mean it.

2032
01:17:46,552 --> 01:17:48,020
IT'S SO GOOD!

2033
01:17:48,253 --> 01:17:50,589
The taste... How do I describe it?

2034
01:17:51,256 --> 01:17:53,091
It's seasoned to perfection.

2035
01:17:53,092 --> 01:17:55,326
I want to try it at home.
I'd love to take some octopus.

2036
01:17:55,327 --> 01:17:57,061
SIGHS

2037
01:17:57,062 --> 01:17:58,863
This is good. I mean it.

2038
01:17:58,864 --> 01:17:59,964
Right?

2039
01:17:59,965 --> 01:18:01,634
- Do-yeon.
- Does it taste amazing?

2040
01:18:02,935 --> 01:18:04,936
A BITE AFTER HEARING THE GOOD REVIEW

2041
01:18:04,937 --> 01:18:07,238
MY GOODNESS

2042
01:18:07,239 --> 01:18:08,806
This is so good.

2043
01:18:08,807 --> 01:18:10,274
The umami is amazing.

2044
01:18:10,275 --> 01:18:11,410
SATISFIED SMILE

2045
01:18:12,177 --> 01:18:14,613
THE PEAKY EATER JAE-HYEON
TAKES A BIG BITE TOO

2046
01:18:14,880 --> 01:18:16,280
You're good, Keun-suk.

2047
01:18:16,281 --> 01:18:17,449
HOUSEMATES ARE HAPPILY DIGGING IN

2048
01:18:17,916 --> 01:18:19,083
All right.

2049
01:18:19,084 --> 01:18:22,021
HAPPY TO HAVE PEOPLE
APPRECIATING HIS FOOD

2050
01:18:22,721 --> 01:18:25,257
FINALLY GETTING STARTED
AFTER SERVING FOOD TO OTHERS

2051
01:18:26,325 --> 01:18:28,359
Hold up. Let me turn this around.

2052
01:18:28,360 --> 01:18:29,794
We shouldn't eat this part.

2053
01:18:29,795 --> 01:18:31,229
- Go for the center.
- Just the center.

2054
01:18:31,230 --> 01:18:33,399
POKING THE POT RICE HERE AND THERE
FOR SOME REASON

2055
01:18:33,666 --> 01:18:35,099
You never know.

2056
01:18:35,100 --> 01:18:37,702
- Let's leave out the charred part.
- Okay.

2057
01:18:37,703 --> 01:18:39,704
- Take the unburnt bit in the center.
- Just that.

2058
01:18:39,705 --> 01:18:42,240
THEY NOTICED THE CHARRED BITS

2059
01:18:42,241 --> 01:18:43,408
THAT CAN'T HAVE HAPPENED

2060
01:18:43,409 --> 01:18:45,877
- Yeah? I haven't tried it yet.
- It's so delicious.

2061
01:18:45,878 --> 01:18:48,847
That part's not burnt, Daniel.

2062
01:18:49,214 --> 01:18:50,582
It's not burnt, just a bit charred.

2063
01:18:51,183 --> 01:18:54,986
YOU'RE SAYING THAT PART ISN'T BURNT?

2064
01:18:54,987 --> 01:18:57,288
The water spattered
from the octopus...

2065
01:18:57,289 --> 01:18:58,724
- No, it's burnt.
- Like scorched rice?

2066
01:18:59,425 --> 01:19:00,959
EMBARRASSED

2067
01:19:01,260 --> 01:19:03,929
EVERYONE DOES A 180
AT HIS SINGLE COMMENT

2068
01:19:04,196 --> 01:19:05,697
Hey, you. It's burnt black.

2069
01:19:05,698 --> 01:19:07,399
I've been protecting you, Keun-suk.

2070
01:19:08,567 --> 01:19:09,702
THAT'S ENOUGH!

2071
01:19:10,035 --> 01:19:12,103
Look at this.
He insisted this wasn't burnt.

2072
01:19:12,104 --> 01:19:14,639
Give it a rest already.
You're so mean.

2073
01:19:14,640 --> 01:19:16,007
You're so mean.

2074
01:19:16,008 --> 01:19:17,076
THAT BACKFIRED ON HIM

2075
01:19:17,876 --> 01:19:18,943
You're the worst.

2076
01:19:18,944 --> 01:19:20,879
We might have a falling-out
sooner than I thought.

2077
01:19:22,281 --> 01:19:23,481
Did I offend you in any way?

2078
01:19:23,482 --> 01:19:24,816
Not at all.

2079
01:19:24,817 --> 01:19:26,884
DOMESTIC PEACE
IS THREATENED FROM DAY 1

2080
01:19:26,885 --> 01:19:29,954
It might not be burnt,
just like Keun-suk said.

2081
01:19:29,955 --> 01:19:31,023
- It's so good.
- The color...

2082
01:19:31,523 --> 01:19:32,623
YUM!

2083
01:19:32,624 --> 01:19:33,691
It's not burnt.

2084
01:19:33,692 --> 01:19:35,193
- Really?
- It's not burnt.

2085
01:19:35,194 --> 01:19:37,596
- Are you sure?
- It must be the octopus ink.

2086
01:19:38,330 --> 01:19:40,331
- It's not burnt.
- It's not charred.

2087
01:19:40,332 --> 01:19:41,934
- It actually tastes better.
- It's not burnt.

2088
01:19:42,167 --> 01:19:43,167
I'm serious. It tastes great.

2089
01:19:43,168 --> 01:19:44,803
It's not burnt. I mean it.

2090
01:19:45,671 --> 01:19:47,773
I love that it has this aroma.
It tastes great.

2091
01:19:49,241 --> 01:19:53,712
NEXT, THEY TRY OCTOPUS COUSCOUS
THAT SHOWS NO HINTS OF BURNING

2092
01:19:54,146 --> 01:19:55,514
A BIG BITE

2093
01:19:56,548 --> 01:19:58,217
POP, POP

2094
01:19:58,684 --> 01:20:00,485
The texture is pretty wild.

2095
01:20:00,486 --> 01:20:01,619
The couscous.

2096
01:20:01,620 --> 01:20:03,522
KEUN-SUK'S FAVORITE DISH
HAS GREAT TEXTURE AND TASTE

2097
01:20:04,156 --> 01:20:06,324
AS FOR THE BLANCHED
EXTRA-LARGE GIANT OCTOPUS

2098
01:20:06,325 --> 01:20:07,425
So good.

2099
01:20:07,426 --> 01:20:10,329
JUST ONE PIECE FILLS YOUR WHOLE MOUTH

2100
01:20:10,763 --> 01:20:11,764
BIG BITE

2101
01:20:12,798 --> 01:20:14,966
Gosh, the onion
somehow improves the taste.

2102
01:20:14,967 --> 01:20:16,534
I didn't realize
when I had the octopus only.

2103
01:20:16,535 --> 01:20:17,902
SOO-JIN KEEPS ON GIVING FEEDBACK

2104
01:20:17,903 --> 01:20:19,471
What a crazy day
we had with that octopus.

2105
01:20:20,172 --> 01:20:23,674
MEANING: THAT WAS A LOT OF WORK,
BUT THANK YOU FOR ENJOYING THEM

2106
01:20:23,675 --> 01:20:25,743
- This gets first place.
- It's ridiculously good.

2107
01:20:25,744 --> 01:20:27,846
WHILE EVERYONE TALKS CHEERFULLY

2108
01:20:28,714 --> 01:20:32,151
ONLY ONE PERSON EATS IN SILENCE

2109
01:20:32,518 --> 01:20:33,718
The aroma...

2110
01:20:33,719 --> 01:20:36,355
A BITE AFTER CHECKING THE SCENT

2111
01:20:37,156 --> 01:20:39,390
The taste somehow got richer.

2112
01:20:39,391 --> 01:20:42,728
NEXT, SHE ADDS
A SLICE OF KIMCHI ON TOP

2113
01:20:43,395 --> 01:20:44,396
BIG BITE

2114
01:20:46,265 --> 01:20:49,268
A BITE OF COUSCOUS FOLLOWS DIRECTLY

2115
01:20:50,335 --> 01:20:51,837
A SINGLE GRAIN ON THE TABLE

2116
01:20:52,538 --> 01:20:55,073
TIDY DA-HEE CLEANS UP IMMEDIATELY

2117
01:20:55,908 --> 01:21:00,179
SHE TRIES EVERY DISH SILENTLY

2118
01:21:00,979 --> 01:21:04,116
BUT HER FACE REMAINS UNREADABLE

2119
01:21:04,416 --> 01:21:06,384
ZONING OUT

2120
01:21:06,385 --> 01:21:08,085
OUT OF THE BLUE

2121
01:21:08,086 --> 01:21:09,621
Hey, AP.

2122
01:21:10,155 --> 01:21:11,589
Hey, AP.

2123
01:21:11,590 --> 01:21:13,492
FROZEN ON THE SPOT

2124
01:21:14,059 --> 01:21:16,694
SWEET YET CHILLING CALL

2125
01:21:16,695 --> 01:21:18,597
When you were cooking earlier

2126
01:21:19,031 --> 01:21:20,731
I was starving.

2127
01:21:20,732 --> 01:21:22,500
TENSES UP

2128
01:21:22,501 --> 01:21:25,336
Honestly, seeing you take out
all the utensils made me go

2129
01:21:25,337 --> 01:21:26,671
"Dang it, Keun-suk."

2130
01:21:26,672 --> 01:21:28,539
That's how I felt
when I was doing the dishes.

2131
01:21:28,540 --> 01:21:29,607
But...

2132
01:21:29,608 --> 01:21:32,109
THESE TWO HAD A MINOR QUARREL

2133
01:21:32,110 --> 01:21:33,811
But now I get it.

2134
01:21:33,812 --> 01:21:34,880
Well...

2135
01:21:35,180 --> 01:21:36,814
You're entitled to do that.
These are so good.

2136
01:21:36,815 --> 01:21:38,050
Totally.

2137
01:21:38,383 --> 01:21:39,550
These are so good.

2138
01:21:39,551 --> 01:21:40,686
Totally.

2139
01:21:42,487 --> 01:21:44,990
DA-HEE'S ENDLESS CLEANING DUTY

2140
01:21:45,657 --> 01:21:49,428
THOUGH THEY'VE LED

2141
01:21:50,429 --> 01:21:51,495
What do you need?

2142
01:21:51,496 --> 01:21:52,763
- Just one tub.
- One tub?

2143
01:21:52,764 --> 01:21:54,632
- Could you clean that as well?
- Which one? This?

2144
01:21:54,633 --> 01:21:57,034
THE HOUSEMATES FIND
THE RIGHT RHYTHM TOGETHER

2145
01:21:57,035 --> 01:22:00,339
LITTLE BY LITTLE,
THEY'RE GETTING USED TO EACH OTHER

2146
01:22:01,106 --> 01:22:03,107
I'm having so much fun.

2147
01:22:03,108 --> 01:22:06,244
If I had been alone
back home at this hour

2148
01:22:06,245 --> 01:22:08,113
I would've just ordered
some fried chicken.

2149
01:22:08,780 --> 01:22:10,781
I would've had a simple dinner

2150
01:22:10,782 --> 01:22:12,717
- and gone to bed.
- Same.

2151
01:22:12,718 --> 01:22:15,554
But here, I got to help a bit.

2152
01:22:16,054 --> 01:22:18,056
The whole waiting
and sharing a meal together

2153
01:22:18,690 --> 01:22:20,825
is extremely awkward,
but also super lovely.

2154
01:22:20,826 --> 01:22:21,927
I enjoyed it immensely.

2155
01:22:25,364 --> 01:22:26,831
I guess humans
aren't meant to live alone.

2156
01:22:26,832 --> 01:22:27,900
For sure.

2157
01:22:28,200 --> 01:22:30,067
Have you heard
how a 1.5-person household

2158
01:22:30,068 --> 01:22:31,470
- is all the rage?
- What's that again?

2159
01:22:31,770 --> 01:22:33,471
It's lonely to live alone, right?

2160
01:22:33,472 --> 01:22:35,339
But it can be a lot
to have a roommate.

2161
01:22:35,340 --> 01:22:37,808
The new idea comes in the middle,
with separate personal quarters

2162
01:22:37,809 --> 01:22:39,678
and a communal space,
just like our arrangement.

2163
01:22:40,145 --> 01:22:41,312
That's the idea.

2164
01:22:41,313 --> 01:22:43,314
The connection
between people in that community

2165
01:22:43,315 --> 01:22:46,250
might not be so close,
but it's still there, all relaxed.

2166
01:22:46,251 --> 01:22:47,318
Yeah.

2167
01:22:47,319 --> 01:22:49,754
I hear many are trying that.
It gets lonely to live alone.

2168
01:22:49,755 --> 01:22:51,990
So they're keeping someone
within an arm's reach.

2169
01:22:52,858 --> 01:22:55,193
Compared to when we first sat down
over there in the living room

2170
01:22:55,761 --> 01:22:57,695
and chatted, all awkwardly

2171
01:22:57,696 --> 01:22:59,664
- we've gotten pretty...
- We've gotten closer.

2172
01:22:59,665 --> 01:23:02,367
- Two meals together did the trick.
- It's going better than I thought.

2173
01:23:02,567 --> 01:23:04,001
Shared meals give people a bond.

2174
01:23:04,002 --> 01:23:05,970
- Right.
- That's so true.

2175
01:23:05,971 --> 01:23:07,171
Shared meals give you a family.

2176
01:23:07,172 --> 01:23:08,640
STARTING TODAY, WE'RE FAMILY

2177
01:23:09,975 --> 01:23:11,810
What was your House Squad Goal?

2178
01:23:12,277 --> 01:23:14,680
Taking photographs.
We've started already.

2179
01:23:15,380 --> 01:23:16,614
<i>I'm building my collection slowly.</i>

2180
01:23:16,615 --> 01:23:19,150
JAE-HYEON'S HOUSE SQUAD GOAL
TAKING PHOTOGRAPHS

2181
01:23:19,151 --> 01:23:21,152
I'd like to try a street performance.

2182
01:23:21,153 --> 01:23:23,055
- A street performance?
- A street performance?

2183
01:23:23,288 --> 01:23:24,555
Do you enjoy singing, Do-yeon?

2184
01:23:24,556 --> 01:23:26,624
- Will you be singing, Da-hee?
- I'm no singer.

2185
01:23:26,625 --> 01:23:28,994
- Come on, you're good at it.
- No, I'm not.

2186
01:23:30,329 --> 01:23:32,063
No, Do-yeon...

2187
01:23:32,064 --> 01:23:33,130
Guys.

2188
01:23:33,131 --> 01:23:34,533
She's an amazing singer.

2189
01:23:35,367 --> 01:23:36,535
What are you talking about?

2190
01:23:37,336 --> 01:23:38,602
What exactly have you seen?

2191
01:23:38,603 --> 01:23:39,770
YOU KNOW ME BETTER THAN I DO?

2192
01:23:39,771 --> 01:23:42,139
- I'm no singer.
- While singing on stage

2193
01:23:42,140 --> 01:23:45,377
she bit into the mic.

2194
01:23:46,011 --> 01:23:49,146
- She ended up bleeding.
- Really?

2195
01:23:49,147 --> 01:23:50,848
- Seriously?
- On live television?

2196
01:24:09,599 --> 01:24:10,667
WHAT ON EARTH?

2197
01:24:10,867 --> 01:24:12,000
A BLOODY PIECE OF MEMORY

2198
01:24:12,001 --> 01:24:13,168
Really?

2199
01:24:13,169 --> 01:24:14,369
People called it

2200
01:24:14,370 --> 01:24:15,771
"blood singing method."

2201
01:24:15,772 --> 01:24:17,173
NAMELY, DRAWING BLOOD TO SING BETTER

2202
01:24:17,841 --> 01:24:19,541
OH, NO

2203
01:24:19,542 --> 01:24:21,744
Let's put on a show together
as Gugi-dong Troupe.

2204
01:24:21,745 --> 01:24:22,946
- "Troupe"?
- Yes.

2205
01:24:23,379 --> 01:24:24,847
Dibs on the circus clown.
I'll learn this.

2206
01:24:24,848 --> 01:24:26,116
Juggling?

2207
01:24:26,549 --> 01:24:28,283
- This?
- I can get us an audience.

2208
01:24:28,284 --> 01:24:29,485
WELCOME TO GUGI-DONG TROUPE'S SHOW

2209
01:24:29,486 --> 01:24:31,788
- Let's go all in.
- Like what?

2210
01:24:32,288 --> 01:24:33,555
We'll get an octopus

2211
01:24:33,556 --> 01:24:34,823
and cook delicious snacks

2212
01:24:34,824 --> 01:24:36,525
- like these.
- And we'll feed people?

2213
01:24:36,526 --> 01:24:38,394
We'll attract folks with food
while Da-hee sings.

2214
01:24:39,362 --> 01:24:40,630
Let's make a big show of it

2215
01:24:41,197 --> 01:24:42,631
with street performances and all.

2216
01:24:42,632 --> 01:24:44,434
IS SHE LEAVING OUT OF EMBARRASSMENT?

2217
01:24:44,701 --> 01:24:46,635
DA-HEE'S HOUSE SQUAD GOAL
GOT TWISTED INTO SOMETHING ELSE

2218
01:24:46,636 --> 01:24:49,071
- Shall we sell grilled octopus arms?
- That could actually work.

2219
01:24:49,072 --> 01:24:50,339
Really? But we'll be outdoors.

2220
01:24:50,340 --> 01:24:51,941
I like the grilled octopus arm idea.

2221
01:24:52,575 --> 01:24:54,077
Good evening, everyone.

2222
01:24:55,278 --> 01:24:56,379
Hold on.

2223
01:24:57,380 --> 01:24:59,616
HERE COMES GUGI-DONG TROUPE'S MC!

2224
01:25:00,016 --> 01:25:02,619
A STUMP OF A GIANT OCTOPUS ARM
INSTEAD OF A MIC

2225
01:25:02,986 --> 01:25:05,087
LAUGHTERS

2226
01:25:05,088 --> 01:25:06,855
You all know Da-hee here, right?

2227
01:25:06,856 --> 01:25:08,624
Do you love Da-hee, everyone?

2228
01:25:08,625 --> 01:25:09,691
- Yes!
- Sure!

2229
01:25:09,692 --> 01:25:11,026
Okay, thank you.

2230
01:25:11,027 --> 01:25:14,997
Do you think TV shows
fully capture Da-hee's charms?

2231
01:25:14,998 --> 01:25:17,299
Today, you'll get to see

2232
01:25:17,300 --> 01:25:18,834
a new side of Da-hee.

2233
01:25:18,835 --> 01:25:20,602
- Shall I go get gloves?
- You rock, Do-yeon!

2234
01:25:20,603 --> 01:25:22,739
Da-hee will now sing <i>Ruby.</i>

2235
01:25:22,972 --> 01:25:25,507
INSTEAD OF A MIC,
A GIANT OCTOPUS ARM IS OFFERED

2236
01:25:25,508 --> 01:25:26,976
What on earth?

2237
01:25:27,877 --> 01:25:29,045
What on earth?

2238
01:25:29,579 --> 01:25:30,647
You've got to sing.

2239
01:25:30,847 --> 01:25:32,281
I work with what I've got.

2240
01:25:32,282 --> 01:25:33,916
I'm not easy to get either.

2241
01:25:33,917 --> 01:25:36,218
You think I want to hold
an octopus arm for a show?

2242
01:25:36,219 --> 01:25:38,720
- I'm the next-generation MC!
- "Next-generation."

2243
01:25:38,721 --> 01:25:41,524
Take the mic from her
so she can start juggling.

2244
01:25:42,959 --> 01:25:44,459
My hands are not free!

2245
01:25:44,460 --> 01:25:45,727
Why bother learning a new skill?

2246
01:25:45,728 --> 01:25:47,996
- I only have one free hand.
- Go on and take it.

2247
01:25:47,997 --> 01:25:49,498
LAUGHING ONE
FUNNY ONE

2248
01:25:49,499 --> 01:25:50,566
ONE LOOKING FOR GLOVES

2249
01:25:50,567 --> 01:25:51,767
Come on, take the mic.

2250
01:25:51,768 --> 01:25:53,869
The octopus arm is too huge.

2251
01:25:53,870 --> 01:25:58,407
A PECULIAR HOUSE SHARE OF ODDBALL

2252
01:25:59,008 --> 01:26:00,608
FIRST MORNING TOGETHER

2253
01:26:00,609 --> 01:26:02,877
HOUSEMATES COME TO REALIZE

2254
01:26:02,878 --> 01:26:04,345
THAT THEY CAN'T HIDE THEIR BARE FACES

2255
01:26:04,346 --> 01:26:07,215
THAT CERTAIN NOISES CROSS WALLS

2256
01:26:07,216 --> 01:26:08,818
AND THAT THERE IS A THIEF AMONG THEM

2257
01:26:09,151 --> 01:26:10,252
CAN THEY GET CLOSER?

2258
01:26:11,253 --> 01:26:12,620
BROUGHT CLOSE BY A SURPRISE EVENT

2259
01:26:12,621 --> 01:26:17,926
DRIVEN APART BY HARSH COMMENTS

2260
01:26:17,927 --> 01:26:19,928
BROUGHT CLOSE BY SERVING LOOKS

2261
01:26:19,929 --> 01:26:23,832
DRIVEN APART BY GOOFY BEHAVIORS

2262
01:26:23,833 --> 01:26:25,200
THEY GROW APART...

2263
01:26:25,201 --> 01:26:28,771
THEY DEFINITELY GROW APART...

2264
01:26:29,004 --> 01:26:31,639
Full of energy and hard-ons...
I mean, heartening stuff.

2265
01:26:31,640 --> 01:26:33,641
- Hard-ons?
- I narrowly avoided a fatal mistake.

2266
01:26:33,642 --> 01:26:35,276
I can't do that.

2267
01:26:35,277 --> 01:26:37,046
<i>Why do I keep calling you bro?</i>

2268
01:26:37,547 --> 01:26:39,547
Dramaday.me
